    Scenario: WHERE after WITH can filter on top of an aggregation
        Given an empty graph
        And having executed:
            """
            CREATE (a {name: 'A'}),
            (b {name: 'B'})
            CREATE (a)-[:REL]->(),
            (a)-[:REL]->(),
            (a)-[:REL]->(),
            (b)-[:REL]->()
            """
        When executing query:
            """
            MATCH (a)-->()
            WITH a, count(*) AS relCount
            WHERE relCount > 1
            RETURN a
            """
        Then the result should be:
            | a             |
            | ({name: 'A'}) |
        And no side effects

